WEBVTT

00:00.501 --> 00:02.044
<i>Previously on "Bitten"...</i>

00:02.085 --> 00:03.295
Clayton: You can't ignore your grief.

00:03.337 --> 00:04.796
You have to deal with Philip's death.

00:04.838 --> 00:06.965
But his sister has been
texting me ever since.

00:07.007 --> 00:08.634
Clayton: I was Bitten when I was ten.

00:08.675 --> 00:10.969
My family couldn't find me,
and eventually they gave up.

00:11.011 --> 00:13.138
Malcolm hasn't had
any money to speak of,

00:13.180 --> 00:14.640
yet he managed an uprising.

00:14.681 --> 00:16.058
Do you think someone is backing him?

00:16.099 --> 00:18.060
You, my friend, are a weasel.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.229
Jeremy, this is a mistake!

00:20.270 --> 00:21.855
You financed the Mutt uprising.

00:21.897 --> 00:23.857
I'm going to finish now what I
should've finished in Stonehaven.

00:23.899 --> 00:25.150
Aaaah!

00:25.192 --> 00:26.610
- Jeremy!
- She isn't here.

00:26.652 --> 00:27.736
Where is Rachel?

00:27.778 --> 00:29.738
I suppose if you kill me
you'll never find out.

00:29.780 --> 00:31.782
Malcolm: Something came
at me in Rochester.

00:31.823 --> 00:33.075
Clayton: Is that what this is about?

00:33.116 --> 00:35.536
You need to keep me alive.
For what's coming.

00:35.577 --> 00:37.746
Wherever they're taking Malcolm Danvers,

00:37.788 --> 00:40.249
is where we're going.

00:43.752 --> 00:46.380
Woman: What's troublin' you, Clayton?

00:46.421 --> 00:48.340
Aren't you excited to see your daddy?

00:48.382 --> 00:50.050
I guess.

00:50.092 --> 00:51.969
He's dyin' to see you.

00:52.010 --> 00:55.556
He went clear 'round the world
to save people in Somalia.

00:55.597 --> 00:57.891
Let's give him a hero's welcome.

00:57.933 --> 00:59.601
What do you say?

01:03.647 --> 01:04.940
(Sigh)

01:06.942 --> 01:10.529
You're always gonna be my
darlin' little man, Clay.

01:10.571 --> 01:12.823
Now and forever.

01:15.117 --> 01:17.077
Okay?

01:17.119 --> 01:18.912
Okay.

01:18.954 --> 01:21.415
All right, go on. Play.

01:21.456 --> 01:23.917
Daddy won't be home for a few hours.

01:26.461 --> 01:29.089
Stay clear of the hollows.

01:29.131 --> 01:32.509
Those Hog Hunters out there will
shoot at anything that moves.

01:32.551 --> 01:48.108
( ♪ )

01:50.319 --> 01:51.987
Who are you?

01:53.530 --> 01:55.449
I'm... Clayton.

01:55.490 --> 01:57.492
Pleasure to meet you, sir.

02:02.623 --> 02:04.458
I'm a real hungry man, Clayton.

02:04.499 --> 02:06.835
I haven't eaten in days.

02:06.877 --> 02:09.338
So this is what I'm proposing:

02:09.378 --> 02:11.298
If you run full speed,

02:11.340 --> 02:12.382
it'll take you I'm guessing, what,

02:12.424 --> 02:14.301
20 minutes to get home?

02:14.343 --> 02:16.678
Do you wanna ch-chase me?

02:19.181 --> 02:20.641
Tell me,

02:20.682 --> 02:24.478
has your hillbilly mom
ever butchered a pig?

02:24.520 --> 02:28.273
Ah, I thought so. Well...

02:28.315 --> 02:31.276
that's what I'm going to do to you.

02:31.318 --> 02:33.946
I'm going to start with your stomach,

02:33.987 --> 02:36.323
then your lungs...

02:36.365 --> 02:38.158
then your heart...

02:38.200 --> 02:39.493
everything.

02:39.535 --> 02:42.538
I'm going to eat them all up.

02:44.373 --> 02:45.916
Are you scared, boy?

02:48.043 --> 02:49.670
Good.

02:49.711 --> 02:52.047
Adrenaline makes the meat taste good.

02:56.218 --> 02:58.011
Run, boy.

02:58.053 --> 02:59.179
<i>Run!</i>

02:59.221 --> 03:08.230
( ♪ )

03:08.272 --> 03:09.940
(Low growling)

03:11.233 --> 03:13.235
(Branch snaps)
(Panting)

03:15.000 --> 03:21.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:22.536 --> 03:24.580
(Snarling)

03:27.374 --> 03:29.209
(Snarl, growl)

03:29.251 --> 03:31.378
(Panicked breathing)

03:34.173 --> 03:35.382
Aaah!

03:35.424 --> 03:36.967
Ah!
(Gunshot)

03:39.219 --> 03:42.055
(Hunters shouting in distance)

03:42.097 --> 03:49.813
( ♪ )

03:51.273 --> 04:06.079
( ♪ )

04:14.796 --> 04:18.800
Sync and corrections
for www.addic7ed.com

04:18.966 --> 04:25.974
Bitten 2x02 - Sworn Enemies
(Feb 14, 2015)

04:27.976 --> 04:40.572
( ♪ )

04:42.282 --> 04:44.284
Jeremy: Is Logan still down there?

04:44.326 --> 04:45.619
Hasn't slept yet.

04:45.661 --> 04:47.829
He won't even take a break to eat.

04:47.871 --> 04:49.581
Jeremy: Malcolm still
hasn't said anything?

04:49.623 --> 04:51.500
Nothing. Not a word

04:51.542 --> 04:52.584
about where he's keeping Rachel.

04:52.626 --> 04:54.461
He's stalling.

04:54.503 --> 04:56.004
Every minute he doesn't say anything

04:56.046 --> 04:58.382
is another minute that
he gets to breathe.

04:58.423 --> 05:00.342
(Cellphone buzzing)

05:03.512 --> 05:04.930
Is that a problem, Elena?

05:06.640 --> 05:07.933
No.

05:09.351 --> 05:10.477
Keeping him alive

05:10.519 --> 05:12.062
is our best option right now.

05:14.356 --> 05:15.941
We finally have him in the cage.

05:17.943 --> 05:20.487
I want to kill him so badly.

05:20.529 --> 05:22.155
As long as there's the possibility

05:22.197 --> 05:23.365
that Rachel is still alive,

05:23.407 --> 05:26.618
we have to conduct
ourselves as if she is.

05:26.660 --> 05:28.370
What about the Alpha council?

05:28.412 --> 05:29.580
Either way, this has to be resolved

05:29.621 --> 05:31.123
before they get back.

05:32.416 --> 05:33.542
If Clay were here,

05:33.584 --> 05:36.253
he'd torture it out of him.

05:36.295 --> 05:38.005
Malcolm isn't swayed by pain,

05:38.046 --> 05:39.214
he enjoys it too much.

05:40.549 --> 05:43.218
Everyone's afraid of something.

05:43.260 --> 05:44.636
Even the devil.

05:44.678 --> 05:59.610
( ♪ )

05:59.651 --> 06:02.905
Clayton: Professor Shayhaus?

06:02.946 --> 06:04.406
I'm Clay Danvers, I called earlier.

06:04.448 --> 06:06.116
Yes, yes, Dr. Danvers.

06:06.158 --> 06:07.534
What can I do for you?

06:07.576 --> 06:11.538
I was fascinated by your
research on pagan symbology.

06:11.580 --> 06:12.956
I came across something recently.

06:12.998 --> 06:14.208
I thought you could help me.

06:14.249 --> 06:16.835
Happy to help. Pre-Celtic symbols

06:16.877 --> 06:19.379
don't get the attention
they deserve anymore.

06:19.421 --> 06:22.007
(Ominous ♪)

06:25.427 --> 06:28.096
Where did you get this?

06:28.138 --> 06:30.265
It was scrawled in a house
in Upstate New York.

06:32.726 --> 06:34.811
With what? What was the medium?

06:36.522 --> 06:37.981
Blood.

06:38.023 --> 06:40.025
I, uh, don't know what it is.

06:40.067 --> 06:41.527
I have a class to teach.

06:41.568 --> 06:43.904
Look, it isn't Christian,
Egyptian or African.

06:43.946 --> 06:47.074
I can't seem to find
any reference to it.

06:47.115 --> 06:49.409
It's not pagan, okay?

06:49.451 --> 06:50.577
I c-can't help you anymore.

06:50.619 --> 06:52.120
But you know what it is.

06:54.248 --> 06:56.500
What do you know about witchcraft?

06:56.542 --> 06:58.001
- Wicca?
- Not Wicca.

06:58.043 --> 07:00.671
This has nothing to do with Wicca.

07:00.712 --> 07:03.465
This is... "left-hand path",

07:03.507 --> 07:04.967
malevolent practice.

07:05.008 --> 07:06.635
Look, take my advice,
burn that piece of paper

07:06.677 --> 07:08.554
and forget you ever saw it.

07:08.595 --> 07:11.598
Or don't. Whatever you do,
I... I can't get involved.

07:11.640 --> 07:14.977
Just point me in the right direction.

07:18.522 --> 07:19.731
Zachary, Louisiana.

07:19.773 --> 07:21.483
- You know it?
- 50 miles North.

07:21.525 --> 07:22.943
Find a Miss Yoruba.

07:22.985 --> 07:24.695
She'll know what kind
of witchcraft that is.

07:24.736 --> 07:26.071
I appreciate it.

07:27.739 --> 07:30.450
Dr. Danvers.

07:30.492 --> 07:32.536
Don't go poking monsters.

07:32.578 --> 07:34.288
It's not a good idea.

07:34.329 --> 07:36.248
Huh!...

07:36.290 --> 07:38.417
I'm not afraid of monsters.

07:42.880 --> 07:46.592
You know, it must've been real hard...

07:46.633 --> 07:49.428
when Jeremy became Alpha instead of you.

07:49.469 --> 07:50.971
Must be tough.

07:51.013 --> 07:53.515
Are you going to
psychoanalyze me, Logan?

07:58.562 --> 08:00.564
Go get some sleep.

08:00.606 --> 08:01.773
C'mon.

08:01.815 --> 08:03.692
We have to find her.

08:03.734 --> 08:05.444
Malcolm: That's right.

08:05.485 --> 08:07.487
How long can a pregnant woman survive

08:07.529 --> 08:09.531
locked away in a dark hole?

08:09.573 --> 08:11.283
Alone and frightened.

08:11.325 --> 08:12.826
Without any food or water.

08:12.868 --> 08:14.703
You let me walk from
Stonehaven in one piece,

08:14.745 --> 08:16.121
and you can have her back.

08:16.163 --> 08:17.539
We will find her.

08:17.581 --> 08:19.541
But on our terms.

08:19.583 --> 08:21.168
Get some rest.

08:21.210 --> 08:22.753
I'm not...

08:22.794 --> 08:24.129
asking you.

08:33.554 --> 08:35.515
Don't be a fool.

08:35.557 --> 08:37.683
There's too much at stake.

08:37.726 --> 08:40.187
You're not walking out of here.

08:43.273 --> 08:45.484
Neither are you, if
you don't listen to me.

08:47.736 --> 08:51.490
There's something coming for us.

08:51.532 --> 08:53.492
Jeremy: No one knows we exist.

08:53.534 --> 08:55.661
So tell me, what's coming for us?

08:57.955 --> 09:01.583
You got in the way
before I could find out.

09:01.625 --> 09:03.836
But whoever he is,

09:03.877 --> 09:06.588
he's strong and he won't stop
until he gets what he wants.

09:06.630 --> 09:08.131
This won't save you.

09:08.173 --> 09:09.800
Whatever you're trying here.

09:12.469 --> 09:16.223
Are you willing to sacrifice
a werewolf child?

09:16.265 --> 09:19.518
The first born in a
generation to your Pack.

09:19.560 --> 09:22.145
I've never known you to negotiate.

09:22.187 --> 09:24.022
What does that tell you?

09:28.610 --> 09:32.406
It tells me that you're afraid.

09:32.447 --> 09:34.241
And I'm enjoying that.

09:34.283 --> 09:49.214
( ♪ )

10:04.354 --> 10:05.856
Hello?

10:08.525 --> 10:09.902
Miss Yoruba?

10:09.943 --> 10:25.000
( ♪ )

10:40.516 --> 10:44.144
(Chickens cackling)

11:12.130 --> 11:13.423
(Snort)

11:14.508 --> 11:16.593
- Are you sure you want to do this?
- Yeah.

11:17.761 --> 11:19.471
(Car door opening)

11:19.513 --> 11:21.431
Jeremy: It's the right thing to do.

11:25.894 --> 11:29.064
Thank you for calling me, Jeremy.

11:29.106 --> 11:30.649
I want to make sure our bad blood

11:30.691 --> 11:33.527
is under the bridge, as you say.

11:33.569 --> 11:35.654
We found Malcolm.

11:35.696 --> 11:39.741
- Where is his body?
- He's in our cage.

11:39.783 --> 11:41.577
He's still alive?

11:45.789 --> 11:48.250
Allow me to kill him.

11:48.292 --> 11:50.043
Our Packs will be bound together,

11:50.085 --> 11:51.712
a united front at the council.

11:51.753 --> 11:53.422
No one will dare go against us.

11:53.463 --> 11:54.673
Well, we haven't forgotten

11:54.715 --> 11:56.508
that you backed Malcolm
in the first place.

12:00.137 --> 12:02.306
You spared my life, of course I...

12:02.347 --> 12:04.016
I defer to you, Jeremy.

12:07.895 --> 12:09.146
Come inside, Rodrigo.

12:12.733 --> 12:15.736
( ♪ )

12:15.777 --> 12:18.322
You've come to your senses?

12:18.363 --> 12:19.865
As a matter of fact, I have.

12:22.784 --> 12:25.579
Seems I bet on the wrong horse.

12:25.621 --> 12:26.622
Time to put it down.

12:26.663 --> 12:41.762
( ♪ )

13:01.865 --> 13:04.034
(Hollow thudding)

13:04.076 --> 13:05.410
(Hollow thuds)

13:16.171 --> 13:18.674
Malcolm: Rodrigo, I need to
talk to the Alpha council.

13:18.715 --> 13:21.927
They have already decided.
They want your head.

13:21.969 --> 13:24.721
This is not about me,
this is about all of us.

13:24.763 --> 13:27.641
Rodrigo: There is no "us", Malcolm.

13:27.683 --> 13:29.184
You're finished.

13:29.226 --> 13:31.103
I don't want you pulling
me down with you.

13:31.144 --> 13:34.773
Rodrigo is here to see the
repercussions of treachery.

13:34.815 --> 13:36.984
So that it doesn't happen again.

13:37.025 --> 13:39.570
It won't, I assure you.

13:39.611 --> 13:41.196
There's a way to guarantee that.

13:47.953 --> 13:50.914
Is there anything you want to
say before I kill you, Malcolm?

13:50.956 --> 13:53.792
You always were an idiot, Rodrigo.

13:53.834 --> 13:55.502
(Flesh ripping)

13:55.544 --> 13:57.880
(Gagging)

13:59.840 --> 14:01.592
There is no cavalry to save you.

14:01.633 --> 14:03.218
Where is she?

14:03.260 --> 14:05.470
If I tell you, you will kill me.

14:05.512 --> 14:06.805
If you don't tell me,

14:06.847 --> 14:08.682
I'm going to kill you right now.

14:08.724 --> 14:12.102
(Eerie mixed whispers)

14:12.144 --> 14:13.812
You won't get a chance.

14:13.854 --> 14:15.063
They're here.

14:16.231 --> 14:26.950
( ♪ )

14:26.992 --> 14:31.038
(Continued mixed whispers)

14:39.838 --> 14:41.298
What is that?

14:41.340 --> 14:42.883
I have no idea.
(Electricity crackling)

14:44.176 --> 14:46.803
(Whispers intensify)

14:49.306 --> 14:52.559
( ♪ )

14:52.601 --> 14:56.063
Mother's voice: You're always gonna
be my darlin' little man, Clay...

14:56.104 --> 15:11.036
( ♪ )

15:36.520 --> 15:37.855
(Shotgun cocking)

15:40.607 --> 15:42.359
Doesn't look like much,

15:42.401 --> 15:45.070
but it sure as shit
ain't open to the public.

15:47.281 --> 15:50.075
A long time ago, maybe 20
years, a family lived here.

15:52.536 --> 15:56.081
Yeah, a Marine.

15:56.123 --> 15:58.041
He was over in Somalia.

15:58.083 --> 16:00.419
I let him park his home here.

16:00.460 --> 16:03.505
Least I could do to support my country.

16:03.547 --> 16:05.507
Had a wife and kid.

16:05.549 --> 16:08.260
Elle, she was a peach.

16:08.302 --> 16:09.469
And the boy...

16:09.511 --> 16:11.597
- Ken or Clem?...
- Clay.

16:11.638 --> 16:14.600
That's right. Wait... you knew them?

16:14.641 --> 16:16.310
Maybe you have a number, a relative,

16:16.351 --> 16:17.728
or just a way to get a hold of them.

16:17.769 --> 16:20.230
Son, the only place you're
going to find that family

16:20.272 --> 16:22.649
is in the cemetery at the edge of town.

16:24.318 --> 16:27.821
Elle was attacked by a wolf.

16:27.863 --> 16:29.865
Elle got killed right
where you're standing.

16:29.907 --> 16:32.409
Th-that brown spot, that's her blood.

16:32.451 --> 16:36.371
We all went searching, but we
never did find the boy's body.

16:36.413 --> 16:40.459
And the Marine? Shoot, he come
home that night from the war,

16:40.501 --> 16:42.044
the whole family gone.

16:42.085 --> 16:44.546
Didn't take too long
till he took a pistol,

16:44.588 --> 16:46.256
put it in his mouth,

16:46.298 --> 16:49.134
and joined them in the great beyond.

16:49.176 --> 16:51.094
Who did you say you was again?

16:51.136 --> 16:52.638
Nobody, I'm nobody. Thanks.

16:52.679 --> 17:00.395
( ♪ )

17:00.437 --> 17:02.481
Open this cage and I'll
tell you where she is.

17:02.523 --> 17:04.942
- Tell me!
- Open this door first.

17:07.569 --> 17:08.737
You don't have her, do you?

17:08.779 --> 17:10.864
Open the goddamn gate!

17:10.906 --> 17:13.825
We are both defenseless here!

17:13.867 --> 17:16.411
No.

17:16.453 --> 17:17.746
We're not.

17:21.834 --> 17:24.837
(Bones cracking)
(Yelling)

17:24.877 --> 17:28.715
( ♪ )

17:28.757 --> 17:31.635
(Continued mixed whispers)

17:33.679 --> 17:36.807
I can't get a bead on which
direction it's coming from.

17:36.849 --> 17:39.518
It's coming from everywhere.

17:39.560 --> 17:40.769
Nick, you circle around from the left,

17:40.811 --> 17:42.312
Elena, you head right.

17:42.354 --> 17:44.565
We'll see if we can surround
whatever's out there.

17:44.606 --> 17:46.567
Be prepared for anything.

17:46.608 --> 17:50.279
(Mixed whispers)

17:52.656 --> 18:00.497
( ♪ )

18:00.539 --> 18:01.748
(Rustling)

18:05.502 --> 18:20.434
( ♪ )

18:49.338 --> 18:50.714
(Panting)

18:50.756 --> 18:54.593
(Faint cries)

19:01.475 --> 19:03.310
(Squealing)

19:05.896 --> 19:07.648
(Speaking in unknown language)

19:08.899 --> 19:17.449
( ♪ )

19:17.491 --> 19:19.284
(Gasping in pain)

19:21.370 --> 19:22.829
(Echo of same phrase)

19:22.871 --> 19:25.582
(Screaming)

19:25.624 --> 19:27.543
Nick: (Continued screams)

19:27.584 --> 19:35.676
( ♪ )

19:35.717 --> 19:37.678
(Mixed whispers, moans)

20:13.922 --> 20:16.633
(Mixed whispers continue)

20:19.595 --> 20:21.221
(Thuds)

20:31.440 --> 20:32.816
(Marble clattering)

20:41.700 --> 20:44.786
(Clinking)

20:44.828 --> 20:46.830
(Continued screaming)

20:46.872 --> 20:47.915
Hey! Hey, hey, hey.

20:47.956 --> 20:49.416
(Screaming) My eyes!

20:49.458 --> 20:50.667
Let me see!

20:50.709 --> 20:51.793
The blood!

20:51.835 --> 20:53.003
It won't stop!

20:53.045 --> 20:54.588
Open your eyes!

20:54.630 --> 20:55.756
(Gasping)

20:55.797 --> 20:57.382
Ah! I can't see anything!

20:57.424 --> 20:59.051
I can't see! I can't see! I'm blind!

20:59.092 --> 21:00.594
Listen to me for one second.

21:00.636 --> 21:01.887
There's no blood.

21:01.929 --> 21:03.055
There's no blood, Nick.

21:03.096 --> 21:04.932
Trust me, there's no blood.

21:04.973 --> 21:06.308
What happened?
(Panting, gasping)

21:06.350 --> 21:08.101
- There's a woman out here...
- What?

21:08.143 --> 21:10.145
She did this to me.
(Panting)

21:10.187 --> 21:11.813
Nick, listen to me very carefully.

21:11.855 --> 21:13.732
Elena is going to take
you back to the house.

21:13.774 --> 21:14.900
I'm going to find the woman.

21:14.942 --> 21:16.485
- Take him back.
- Okay.

21:16.527 --> 21:17.945
Elena: Follow me. It's okay.

21:17.986 --> 21:19.071
Listen to my voice. You're okay.

21:19.112 --> 21:29.706
( ♪ )

21:29.748 --> 21:30.874
(Snarling)

21:30.916 --> 21:34.837
(Growling, snarling)

21:34.878 --> 21:37.589
(Rattling)

21:37.631 --> 21:41.635
( ♪ )

21:41.677 --> 21:43.053
God...

21:43.095 --> 21:44.137
Okay, listen to my voice.

21:44.179 --> 21:46.390
(Panting)

21:46.431 --> 21:48.725
- Do you feel my hands?
- Yes.

21:48.767 --> 21:49.935
Okay. Good.

21:49.977 --> 21:51.728
Do you feel this?

21:51.770 --> 21:53.230
Yeah, yeah.

21:53.272 --> 21:55.858
They're not wet. There's no blood.

21:55.899 --> 21:57.067
Breathe.

21:57.109 --> 21:59.862
There's no blood.

21:59.903 --> 22:01.446
You're okay.

22:01.488 --> 22:03.657
(Slower panting)

22:03.699 --> 22:05.075
Okay?

22:10.873 --> 22:12.833
This is like a bad dream.

22:12.875 --> 22:14.293
(Electricity buzzing)

22:20.591 --> 22:22.843
(Birds chirping)

22:29.057 --> 22:30.434
Get any sleep?

22:30.475 --> 22:33.395
I slept standing up.

22:33.437 --> 22:34.646
I'll take the next watch.

22:34.688 --> 22:35.689
You've been up for 20 hours,

22:35.731 --> 22:37.524
you should go to bed.

22:37.566 --> 22:40.110
Jeremy didn't find
a single trace of them.

22:40.152 --> 22:41.945
I don't like how they just
showed up and then disappeared

22:41.987 --> 22:43.405
like we hallucinated the whole thing.

22:43.447 --> 22:44.865
Whatever it was,

22:44.907 --> 22:46.617
I think they were trying
to get to Malcolm.

22:46.658 --> 22:48.076
It can't be ghosts, because...

22:48.118 --> 22:50.245
You know I... I don't believe in ghosts.

22:50.287 --> 22:51.705
Neither do you.

22:51.747 --> 22:54.082
Right?

22:54.124 --> 22:56.043
There was a time if you
told me werewolves existed,

22:56.084 --> 22:57.419
I would've laughed.

22:59.087 --> 23:01.465
I don't laugh at much anymore.

23:01.507 --> 23:02.633
That's not reassuring.

23:04.676 --> 23:06.136
You're not going out there?

23:08.305 --> 23:09.806
I don't have a choice.

23:13.101 --> 23:15.687
Philip's sister is here?

23:15.729 --> 23:17.606
In Bear Valley.

23:17.648 --> 23:18.732
Whatever Philip told her...

23:18.774 --> 23:20.526
Jorge cleaned everything!

23:20.567 --> 23:23.028
There's nothing that
traces back to you, or us,

23:23.070 --> 23:24.988
or any of Malcolm's associates.

23:25.030 --> 23:26.782
As far as the world is concerned,

23:26.823 --> 23:28.116
Philip died in a car accident.

23:28.158 --> 23:30.702
Yeah, but his sister is here.

23:30.744 --> 23:33.080
Do you really want her
driving up to the front door?

23:41.588 --> 23:44.508
Hey, if you see any strange
women with white eyes,

23:44.550 --> 23:45.759
run them over.

23:45.801 --> 23:52.599
( ♪ )

23:52.641 --> 23:55.435
Malcolm: I don't know
what happened out there.

23:55.477 --> 23:56.979
I'm in here.

23:57.020 --> 23:58.814
What happened to your men in Rochester?

24:04.069 --> 24:07.447
At first I thought
it was you coming at us.

24:07.489 --> 24:10.742
They were human, except for one thing.

24:12.536 --> 24:14.204
They didn't feel any pain.

24:16.790 --> 24:18.625
Where's Rachel?

24:18.667 --> 24:21.461
I had her safely tucked
away before the attack.

24:21.503 --> 24:23.463
After, well...

24:23.505 --> 24:25.591
Let's just say now
I have bigger worries.

24:29.511 --> 24:32.181
There are dark forces at work.

24:32.222 --> 24:35.684
Forces we never believed
could exist, but they do.

24:35.726 --> 24:37.144
Clayton: Witchcraft.

24:41.106 --> 24:44.651
I found what you were looking for.

24:44.693 --> 24:48.530
That woman you killed
had it hidden away.

24:48.572 --> 24:51.283
That symbol is in here.

24:53.785 --> 24:57.164
She died protecting that book.

24:57.206 --> 24:59.750
You have to understand
them to fight them.

24:59.791 --> 25:02.419
That book is the key.

25:02.461 --> 25:04.713
Give it to me.

25:04.755 --> 25:06.423
Tell me where Rachel is.

25:06.465 --> 25:15.724
( ♪ )

25:15.766 --> 25:18.268
You'll never survive this.

25:18.310 --> 25:21.563
You saw what they did
to a house full of wolves.

25:21.605 --> 25:23.357
It took no time.

25:28.779 --> 25:43.877
( ♪ )

25:58.350 --> 25:59.518
Hi.

25:59.560 --> 26:00.644
(Sniffling)

26:06.859 --> 26:08.235
(Clearing throat)

26:14.533 --> 26:16.869
I am so sorry.

26:18.287 --> 26:19.621
I couldn't...

26:19.663 --> 26:22.249
I couldn't bring myself
to come to his funeral.

26:24.418 --> 26:26.795
I've been trying to figure
out where it all went wrong.

26:29.673 --> 26:31.717
Philip started acting jealous,

26:31.758 --> 26:34.386
ranting about how you were
part of some crime family.

26:34.428 --> 26:36.972
At first I thought: nervous breakdown.

26:39.600 --> 26:42.394
And then he was stabbed
in his own apartment.

26:45.272 --> 26:48.483
Just tell me straight, Elena.

26:48.525 --> 26:51.320
Did Clay do that?

26:51.361 --> 26:52.863
What?

26:52.905 --> 26:54.615
No, no, Clay would not do that.

26:54.656 --> 26:56.992
He tried to protect Philip.

26:57.034 --> 26:59.912
You got my brother mixed
up into something.

26:59.953 --> 27:02.539
And now he's dead.

27:02.581 --> 27:06.793
( ♪ )

27:06.835 --> 27:09.880
Philip wasn't having
a nervous breakdown.

27:09.922 --> 27:11.256
When he had his accident,

27:11.298 --> 27:14.843
he was racing to the airport to meet me.

27:14.885 --> 27:16.428
We were going to fly to France together.

27:16.470 --> 27:18.430
There were some very
bad people after me.

27:18.472 --> 27:20.265
You're a photographer, Elena.

27:20.307 --> 27:21.683
You're not a mobster.

27:21.725 --> 27:24.937
It's because of my family.

27:24.978 --> 27:28.440
There is a darkness there.

27:28.482 --> 27:30.943
Death, and... and murder.

27:30.984 --> 27:32.528
And I was a part of it.

27:34.613 --> 27:35.739
I tried to run.

27:35.781 --> 27:36.907
I tried to start a new life.

27:36.949 --> 27:38.617
And your brother, you,

27:38.659 --> 27:42.663
your entire family were my lifeline.

27:42.704 --> 27:46.416
He was going to save me from my past.

27:47.668 --> 27:49.044
He couldn't.

27:49.086 --> 27:50.587
Because it came and found me.

27:50.629 --> 27:53.549
You should've gone to the police, Elena.

27:53.590 --> 27:55.843
No. Listen to me.

27:57.427 --> 27:59.763
In the end, Philip understood
he couldn't do that,

27:59.805 --> 28:00.973
it wasn't possible.

28:01.014 --> 28:03.475
It's why we decided to run.

28:03.517 --> 28:05.769
I have spent the last week lashing out

28:05.811 --> 28:07.312
at everything around me,

28:07.354 --> 28:10.107
trying to find someone
to blame for his death.

28:10.148 --> 28:12.609
And I figured out who's responsible.

28:15.028 --> 28:16.613
It's me.

28:16.655 --> 28:18.323
It is my fault.

28:18.365 --> 28:20.075
I could not do the one thing

28:20.117 --> 28:21.451
that would've saved his life.

28:21.493 --> 28:22.786
I couldn't leave him.

28:23.871 --> 28:25.747
If I'd just left him,

28:25.789 --> 28:26.999
he'd have a broken heart

28:27.040 --> 28:30.294
but he would still be alive.

28:30.335 --> 28:32.337
Philip wasn't prepared for the evil

28:32.379 --> 28:34.798
that came into his life...

28:37.050 --> 28:38.343
Me.

28:40.596 --> 28:42.848
Did you ever really love him?

28:46.435 --> 28:47.978
I thought I did.

28:52.024 --> 28:54.985
It wasn't enough. I'm sorry.

28:55.027 --> 28:56.945
- I don't know you.
- Diane...

28:56.987 --> 28:59.364
- I don't want to know you.
- Diane...

28:59.406 --> 29:02.492
Don't worry, I'm not going
to go to the police.

29:02.534 --> 29:04.494
What the hell would I tell them, anyway?

29:04.536 --> 29:06.330
My best friend was a criminal.

29:06.371 --> 29:08.040
What kind? I don't know, she won't say.

29:08.081 --> 29:10.667
You have every right to hate me.

29:10.709 --> 29:13.837
(Sniffling)

29:13.879 --> 29:17.674
So much hurt.

29:17.716 --> 29:19.843
For what?

29:19.885 --> 29:21.345
Money? Power?

29:21.386 --> 29:23.847
What is it you people fight for?

29:23.889 --> 29:26.391
Right now... revenge.

29:30.437 --> 29:32.856
(Footsteps departing)

29:34.191 --> 29:38.612
Don't ever contact me
or my family again.

29:38.654 --> 29:40.572
And I'll return the favour.

29:47.746 --> 29:57.422
( ♪ )

29:59.675 --> 30:01.218
Are you telling me we're
going to summon these things

30:01.260 --> 30:03.762
with orange pekoe? You're shitting me.

30:03.804 --> 30:06.348
Clayton: Why hide the book
if these spells aren't real?

30:07.850 --> 30:11.436
<i>Veni ad me, in nomine lunae.</i>

30:17.734 --> 30:20.028
Maybe we should've used chamomile.

30:20.070 --> 30:22.531
(Mixed whispers; rumbling)

30:27.536 --> 30:29.788
(Loud clattering)

30:29.830 --> 30:45.137
( ♪ )

30:48.599 --> 30:50.100
<i>I wouldn't do that, big guy.</i>

30:50.142 --> 30:51.768
- Clay...
- Trust me, I wouldn't.

30:53.520 --> 30:55.856
Woman: Well, you obviously
know that we are witches.

30:55.898 --> 30:59.193
And we know that you are werewolves.

30:59.234 --> 31:01.862
Let's get that out of
the way so we can begin.

31:01.904 --> 31:03.947
Can't believe we summoned witches.

31:03.989 --> 31:05.657
Woman: You didn't summon us.

31:05.699 --> 31:07.659
We came because it's time to talk.

31:07.701 --> 31:10.412
Oh, and you left your
front door unlocked.

31:12.706 --> 31:14.875
We heard you in there: "veni ad me".

31:14.917 --> 31:16.793
It's too bad that we
know way more about you

31:16.835 --> 31:19.004
than you know about us.

31:19.046 --> 31:21.423
Seems you have us at
a disadvantage, then.

31:21.465 --> 31:23.425
Again, more than you know.

31:24.635 --> 31:26.428
Sit.

31:26.470 --> 31:27.638
Whoa.

31:27.679 --> 31:28.764
Woman: Paige.

31:30.516 --> 31:31.934
My apologies.

31:31.975 --> 31:34.603
It seems the young
think that showing off

31:34.645 --> 31:36.939
is a virtue.

31:36.980 --> 31:39.525
Jeremy: Clay, Logan.

31:39.566 --> 31:41.735
Would you please guard the entrances?

31:41.777 --> 31:43.570
No more surprises.

31:43.612 --> 31:53.789
( ♪ )

31:53.830 --> 31:55.749
With your permission.

31:55.791 --> 31:57.417
Jeremy: Please.

31:57.459 --> 32:12.349
( ♪ )

32:16.061 --> 32:17.771
I guess we all like to show off

32:17.813 --> 32:19.565
from time to time.

32:19.606 --> 32:21.775
My name is Ruth Winterbourne.

32:21.817 --> 32:23.610
My associate, Paige.

32:23.652 --> 32:26.780
You'll forgive me if I'm not
familiar with the protocols

32:26.822 --> 32:28.615
dealing with your type.

32:28.657 --> 32:30.659
We're witches. You can say it.

32:30.701 --> 32:33.412
It's not a word we like
to use in unsafe company,

32:33.453 --> 32:35.372
but with you, it's fine

32:35.414 --> 32:36.957
since you're both from the Other World.

32:36.999 --> 32:38.792
"The Other World"?

32:38.834 --> 32:40.711
Ruth: Not human.

32:40.752 --> 32:41.962
Supernatural.

32:42.004 --> 32:44.548
You might prefer "special".

32:44.590 --> 32:47.759
Magic, as you might call it, does exist.

32:47.801 --> 32:49.761
We don't fly around on broomsticks

32:49.803 --> 32:52.139
or twitch our noses to cast spells.

32:52.181 --> 32:54.600
I run a successful cosmetic company.

32:54.641 --> 32:56.602
Wholly organic, of course.

32:56.643 --> 32:58.729
We have more in common than you think.

32:58.770 --> 33:02.107
We both need to keep
our existence a secret.

33:02.149 --> 33:04.067
People panic at the thought of us.

33:04.109 --> 33:07.112
Always have, always will.

33:07.154 --> 33:11.116
I have no interest in
exposing you... or us.

33:11.158 --> 33:13.785
You're all women, I take it?

33:13.827 --> 33:15.913
Our power is hereditary, like yours.

33:15.954 --> 33:17.998
But unlike you, we only give birth

33:18.040 --> 33:19.625
to female children.

33:19.666 --> 33:21.084
How do you know so much about us?

33:21.126 --> 33:23.629
We... keep tabs,

33:23.670 --> 33:26.131
but we don't intervene in your affairs.

33:26.173 --> 33:28.842
"Live and let live" is our motto.

33:30.886 --> 33:33.013
Yet here you are.

33:33.055 --> 33:34.806
In my home.

33:34.848 --> 33:37.518
Calling us out into the woods.

33:37.559 --> 33:40.062
Were you responsible for
what happened in Rochester?

33:40.103 --> 33:42.397
All we saw was the aftermath.

33:42.439 --> 33:45.984
The man that did that knows we exist.

33:46.026 --> 33:47.569
All of us.

33:50.072 --> 33:51.949
We're being hunted.

33:54.618 --> 33:57.955
They want the werewolf
that you have downstairs.

33:57.996 --> 33:59.873
And so do we.

34:02.835 --> 34:04.503
(Door opening)

34:04.545 --> 34:05.796
If you're sneaking in,

34:05.838 --> 34:07.923
you must have vengeance on your mind.

34:09.049 --> 34:11.510
Why did you kill Philip?

34:11.552 --> 34:13.679
You set him up just to kill him.

34:13.719 --> 34:16.598
Why? Just to be a
sadistic son of a bitch?

34:18.058 --> 34:19.810
You needed to know who's boss.

34:21.143 --> 34:24.063
You are not in control.

34:24.106 --> 34:26.315
- You never were.
- Not me.

34:27.609 --> 34:30.946
Your nature is in control.

34:30.987 --> 34:33.824
Like it or not, you're a werewolf.

34:33.866 --> 34:36.618
You are bound to our
ways by your biology

34:36.659 --> 34:38.579
and it will not be denied.

34:40.581 --> 34:44.001
Do you still have that silly dream

34:44.042 --> 34:45.752
of living in Toronto?

34:50.841 --> 34:54.511
It's so terribly mundane
and superficial.

34:55.929 --> 34:57.931
Do you feel it?

34:57.973 --> 35:01.226
The rage? The lust?

35:01.268 --> 35:03.896
It is your power.

35:03.937 --> 35:05.480
You can thank me, Elena,

35:05.522 --> 35:07.232
'cause I gave you the
greatest gift of all:

35:07.274 --> 35:08.942
your true self.

35:08.984 --> 35:13.071
You are now all wolf.

35:13.113 --> 35:15.324
You are our future.

35:15.365 --> 35:17.284
I just want to put you in the past.

35:19.620 --> 35:20.954
Ruth: You want him dead.

35:20.996 --> 35:22.623
We want to trade him.

35:22.664 --> 35:23.916
For what?

35:23.957 --> 35:25.584
For a young girl.

35:25.626 --> 35:28.754
A young witch who hasn't
yet come into her powers.

35:28.795 --> 35:31.298
She can't defend herself.

35:31.340 --> 35:33.217
She was kidnapped by this force.

35:34.760 --> 35:36.053
Look, all you need to know

35:36.094 --> 35:38.931
is that we want her back.

35:38.972 --> 35:40.474
Help us.

35:41.808 --> 35:43.060
Please.

35:45.270 --> 35:48.232
You want Malcolm.

35:48.273 --> 35:50.275
But I can't turn him over.

35:50.317 --> 36:04.414
( ♪ )

36:04.456 --> 36:07.167
You think brute force will be enough.

36:08.836 --> 36:10.254
Well, it won't be.

36:11.797 --> 36:13.173
Soon they will come for you

36:13.215 --> 36:17.010
and you will be begging for our help.

36:22.015 --> 36:23.058
I doubt that.

36:23.100 --> 36:24.309
Doubt all you like,

36:24.351 --> 36:26.186
but let me tell you this.

36:26.228 --> 36:28.397
We've managed to survive a long time...

36:28.438 --> 36:30.816
much longer than you, I might add...

36:30.858 --> 36:33.402
and we didn't do it by playing nice.

36:33.443 --> 36:36.738
You're either on our side
or you're in our way.

36:36.780 --> 36:38.699
Right now, you're in our way.

36:44.872 --> 36:46.832
I've been waiting for this long enough.

36:46.874 --> 36:48.166
That's right.

36:48.208 --> 36:50.335
Feel it in your veins, in your blood.

36:50.377 --> 36:52.129
You know you want it!

36:52.171 --> 36:54.047
No more manipulations.

36:54.089 --> 36:55.382
Your lessons are over.

36:55.424 --> 36:57.092
It's time for you to die.
(Bars clanging)

36:57.134 --> 36:59.011
Then open this door.

36:59.052 --> 37:00.762
Let's settle this.

37:00.804 --> 37:02.890
I made Clay, he made you,

37:02.931 --> 37:04.766
and it's only fitting
that you're the one.

37:04.808 --> 37:06.226
Blood will out!

37:07.644 --> 37:10.606
I am going to rip the life out of you!

37:10.647 --> 37:13.108
You want to see the wolf? Huh?

37:13.150 --> 37:14.735
(Shouting)
Here I am!

37:16.570 --> 37:18.906
(Clattering)

37:21.116 --> 37:23.035
No, Elena!

37:23.076 --> 37:24.620
(Cell door clanging)

37:24.661 --> 37:26.246
(Effort grunts)

37:26.288 --> 37:28.832
Malcolm: That's it, girl, come at me!

37:28.874 --> 37:30.918
What the hell were you thinking?
(Panting)

37:30.959 --> 37:32.294
I'm sorry, Logan.

37:32.336 --> 37:34.046
I loved her too, but he has to die.

37:34.087 --> 37:35.923
You have to die!

37:35.964 --> 37:37.925
Take her upstairs.

37:37.966 --> 37:39.510
(Departing footsteps)

37:40.761 --> 37:42.137
Malcolm: You see that, Clay?

37:42.179 --> 37:43.889
She's got fight in her.

37:43.931 --> 37:46.099
She's better than all
of you put together.

37:46.141 --> 37:48.143
You want to see fight?

37:48.185 --> 37:51.980
I knew as soon as you got back.

37:52.022 --> 37:55.275
Did you hear some stories
in Baton Rouge, Clay?

37:55.317 --> 37:59.029
Tale of the woman eaten alive
in her trailer by a wolf?

37:59.071 --> 38:01.782
Crying for her son

38:01.823 --> 38:04.785
as I tore her to bits?

38:04.826 --> 38:06.161
(Shout)
(Bars banging)

38:14.837 --> 38:18.549
(Measured exhalation, deep breath)

38:24.847 --> 38:26.682
Hey...

38:26.723 --> 38:29.017
Hey, it's okay. I'm here now.

38:33.105 --> 38:36.108
You were right, Clay.

38:36.149 --> 38:39.820
I need to deal with Philip's murder.

38:39.862 --> 38:42.239
You had no part in it.

38:42.281 --> 38:44.283
No.

38:44.324 --> 38:45.784
I was about to throw away

38:45.826 --> 38:48.412
Logan's last chance at finding Rachel.

38:50.622 --> 38:53.792
I don't know what I'm
capable of anymore.

38:53.834 --> 38:55.878
I want you to find peace.

38:58.172 --> 38:59.840
(Whispering)
Me too.

38:59.882 --> 39:15.022
( ♪ )

39:29.953 --> 39:31.538
(Panting)

39:38.337 --> 39:41.256
All of these plans that we make,

39:41.298 --> 39:43.800
formulating strategies,

39:43.842 --> 39:47.679
guiding our futures through
Machiavellian means.

39:47.721 --> 39:50.140
All designed to get us what we want.

39:52.643 --> 39:55.270
You never did have the stomach for that.

39:55.312 --> 39:57.731
Much to my eternal shame.

40:03.779 --> 40:06.198
Your design was interrupted, though.

40:06.240 --> 40:07.741
You couldn't have foreseen

40:07.783 --> 40:09.326
that you'd be flushed out
of that hole in Rochester

40:09.368 --> 40:10.744
by an unknown force.

40:10.786 --> 40:13.497
That wasn't part of your plan.

40:13.539 --> 40:16.291
As usual, you struggle to make a point.

40:16.333 --> 40:18.210
(Chuckle)

40:18.252 --> 40:20.921
You don't have her.

40:20.963 --> 40:24.258
You have no idea where she is.

40:24.299 --> 40:27.678
And your last bargaining
chip is off the table.

40:34.852 --> 40:37.271
You will not survive what's coming.

40:38.856 --> 40:39.940
Yeah.

40:42.234 --> 40:44.820
Whatever is out there,

40:44.862 --> 40:47.781
these witches, whoever knows about us,

40:47.823 --> 40:51.952
I will deal with them for
the protection of my Pack.

40:51.994 --> 40:53.328
My family.

40:56.540 --> 40:58.959
And you will not be around to see it.

41:01.920 --> 41:03.714
You will soon join me.

41:05.674 --> 41:08.302
I spent most of my life afraid of you.

41:11.305 --> 41:12.806
Not anymore.

41:15.809 --> 41:18.061
Make peace with yourself, Dad.

41:19.396 --> 41:21.106
First light will be your last.

41:21.148 --> 41:33.827
( ♪ )

41:42.252 --> 41:44.379
- You okay?
- Yeah.

41:45.923 --> 41:47.216
It's over, isn't it?

41:50.552 --> 41:53.180
Malcolm doesn't know anything, Logan.

41:56.058 --> 41:57.851
We have to come to terms with that.

41:59.186 --> 42:02.814
(Stammering)
You... you heard those witches.

42:02.856 --> 42:05.442
That guy that came after Malcolm...

42:05.484 --> 42:07.236
She-she was in that house.

42:07.277 --> 42:09.279
I mean, if he wanted a
werewolf, maybe, maybe...

42:09.321 --> 42:11.907
maybe he took her.

42:11.949 --> 42:15.202
